description: A factory photo op for Alexander Lukashenko backfires when workers demand his resignation.
title: Belarus protests: Workers boo Lukashenko as election unrest spreads
title_page: Belarus protests: Workers boo Lukashenko as election unrest spreads - BBC News
maintext: Six years on, could Russia's military intervene in Belarus? On paper, at least, such a move would appear counter-productive. The opposition movement in Belarus is not anti-Russia/pro-Europe - it is anti-Lukashenko. If Russia were to send in troops to shore up the Belarusian leader, it risks alienating the Belarusian people and creating anti-Moscow sentiment.
